              "blocks": {
                "accordion_row_fzwYhJ": {
                  "type": "_accordion-row",
                  "settings": {
                    "heading": "Dispatch Coordinator | London, UK",
                    "open_by_default": false,
                    "icon": "none",
                    "width": 20
                  },
                  "blocks": {
                    "text_bY3Ypf": {
                      "type": "text",
                      "settings": {
                        "text": "<p><strong>The Role</strong></p><p>MWL is seeking a full-time Dispatch Coordinator to join our Logistics team based in London, UK.This role is ideal for a highly organised, proactive individual who thrives in a fast-paced environment and takes pride in precision, care, and teamwork. You will play a pivotal role in the final stage of each bride’s journey, ensuring every gown leaves our warehouse packed beautifully, accurately, and on time.Working on-site, you will collaborate closely with the wider MWL team, supporting daily logistics operations while contributing to a smooth, efficient, and detail-driven dispatch process.</p><p><strong>Role Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Carefully pack and dispatch wedding dresses, ensuring each piece is prepared with care, precision, and attention to detail</li><li>Ensure all shipments are packed securely so dresses arrive in pristine condition</li><li>Update backend systems to maintain accurate and up-to-date logistics and stock records</li><li>Create and manage labels, documentation, and shipment paperwork</li><li>Support stock management and general warehouse organisation</li><li>Carry out administrative tasks including reporting, database entry, and printing</li><li>Provide additional operational support as directed by the Operations Manager</li></ul><p><strong>Skills & Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>Exceptional attention to detail with a strong commitment to accuracy and quality</li><li>Ability to manage multiple tasks simultaneously while maintaining organisation and efficiency</li><li>Strong organisational and administrative skills</li><li>Comfortable working under pressure in a fast-paced, hands-on environment</li><li>Collaborative team player who enjoys supporting others and contributing to shared goals</li><li>An appreciation for fashion and bridal, with an understanding of the importance of a wedding dress in a bride’s journey</li></ul><p><strong>About You:</strong></p><ul><li>You are meticulous and detail-oriented in everything you do</li><li>You are highly organised and proactive by nature</li><li>You have a genuine passion for fashion and bridal</li><li>You enjoy working as part of a team and take pride in doing things properly </li></ul><p><strong>Apply by:<br/><br/>Email</strong> | <a href=\"mailto:tove@mwlbride.com\">tove@mwlbride.com</a></p>",
                        "width": "100%",
