                "accordion_row_yj78wD": {
                  "type": "_accordion-row",
                  "settings": {
                    "heading": "Social Media & PR Manager | Gold Coast, Australia",
                    "open_by_default": false,
                    "icon": "none",
                    "width": 20
                  },
                  "blocks": {
                    "text_PcEMT3": {
                      "type": "text",
                      "settings": {
                        "text": "<p><strong>The Role</strong></p><p>MWL is looking for a creative and highly passionate <strong>Social Media & PR Manager</strong> to lead MWL’s digital presence and drive the next phase of our global brand story.</p><p>This is a hands-on strategic role for someone who’s equally comfortable setting the vision as they are executing it. Driving the visual & influencer strategy, staying ahead of elevated trend forecasting with strong storytelling instincts.</p><p>You’ll be the pulse of the brand: Leading our social media strategy, nurturing influencer and PR relationships, ensuring MWL continues to set the tone in modern bridal.</p><p><strong>What you’ll do:</strong></p><p>• Drive strategy across all channels –Instagram, TikTok, Pinterest & LinkedIn, setting direction, tone, and visual rhythm in line with brand’s aesthetics and goals</p><p>• Oversee day-to-day execution of content scheduling and planning. You'll be supported by a full time in house Content Creator and Graphic Designer</p><p>• Collaborate closely with the TikTok Manager and Content Creator to ensure content output is cohesive, consistent, and aligned with brand strategy</p><p>• Brief content as per strategy working as afar ahead as possible</p><p>• Maintain and update the social media calendar, ensuring all activity is synced with campaigns, launches, and marketing milestones</p><p>• Be the first to spot trends and creators to identify how MWL can authentically join the conversation and collaborate</p><p>• Lead influencer and UGC strategy – from identifying newly engaged brides to securing placements with fashion and lifestyle creators</p><p>• Liaise with creators and influencers to maintain an ongoing stream of content, ensuring MWL remains aspirational and visible across platforms</p><p>• Oversee press & PR outreach for new campaigns and key brand moments - creating and maintaining relationships with bridal directories</p><p>• Support the marketing team in storytelling through key moments – product launches, brand campaigns and international events</p><p><strong>You’ll thrive if you:</strong></p><p>• Have experience in social media, PR or influencer marketing – ideally within fashion, beauty or lifestyle (but not limited to)</p><p>• Ensure creatives are always engaging across all MWL platforms – from Instagram reels to stills, stories and editorial snippets</p><p>• Be obsessed with culture and always two steps ahead of the trend curve</p><p>• Feel confident establishing organic strategy and optimising for maximum growth</p><p>• Understand how to blend data-driven decisions with instinctive creativity</p><p>• Feel confident briefing, directing and collaborating both internally and with external partners</p><p>• Love storytelling, visual strategy, and all things social</p><p><strong>Apply by:</strong><br/><br/><strong>Email</strong> | genea@mwlbride.com</p><p><strong>SEEK</strong> | view listing <a href=\"https://www.seek.com.au/job/89011007?ref=hirer-jobs-list\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.seek.com.au/job/89011007?ref=hirer-jobs-list\">here</a>. </p>",
                        "width": "100%",
                        "max_width": "normal",
                        "alignment": "left",
                        "type_preset": "custom",
                        "enable_mobile_size": false,
